### 2️⃣ Why idempotency is REQUIRED (not optional)
Because Sidekiq guarantees:

At-least-once execution

This means a job can run more than once.

Real reasons jobs run twice

Sidekiq process crashes mid-job
Redis goes down after DB commit
Worker timeout
Manual retry from UI
Deploy restart
Network failure
Duplicate enqueue

If a worker crashes after completing work but before acknowledging Redis, the job will be retried.

